Name: The Sting-Rays
rawData:
The Sting-Rays (often credited The Stingrays) were a British Garage Rock and Psychobilly band from Greater London which recorded on Ace Records' garage and psychedelic subsidiary Big Beat and Joe Foster's Kaleidoscope Sound in the 1980s.
Most of the band's songs were written by Alec Palao and Bal Croce

Also known as: The Bananamen, The Paralyzed Purple Rays
Origin: Crouch End, Haringey, Greater London, England
Associated acts: The Earls of Suave, The Sneetches
